    • Method Detail

      • getWeatherStations

        public WeatherStation[] getWeatherStations()
        Returns all weather stations in the database in no particular order
        Returns:
        an array containing all weather stations that are in this database. Note that the size of the array should be equal to the result of this.numberOfWeatherStations().

      • numberOfWeatherStations

        public int numberOfWeatherStations()
        Returns the number of weather stations in the database
        Returns:
        the number of weather stations in this database

      • addWeatherStation

        public WeatherDatabase addWeatherStation​(WeatherStation station)
        adds a weather station to this database
        Parameters:
        station - is the weather station to add. It will always be non-null.
        Returns:
        this weather station.

      • removeWeatherStation

        public boolean removeWeatherStation​(int id)
        removes weather station with given id from this database
        Parameters:
        id - is the ID number of the weather station to remove.
        Returns:
        true if the specified weather station is successfully removed, returns false otherwise (i.e., if there was no weather station with the specified ID number in this database to begin with).

      • getMaxTemperature

        public int getMaxTemperature()
        returns the highest temperature ever recorded by any weather station in the data base.

      • getMaxTemperature

        public Temperature getMaxTemperature​(int day)
        returns the highest temperature on a specified day that is recorded in a report in the weather stations in this database.
        Parameters:
        day - is the day to find the max temperature on. Note that this might be the special max temperature day that a weather station records.
        Returns:
        the temperature object with the highest recorded Temperature in the data base on the specified day.

      • averageTemperature

        public double averageTemperature​(int startDay,
                                 int endDay)
        Computes the average temperature (over all weather stations) for the time period starting at startDay and ending at endDay (inclusive)
        Parameters:
        startDay - is the starting day
        endDay - is the ending endDay
        Returns:
        the average temperature of all temperature reports for the time period startDay to endDay (inclusive) taken from all weather stations in this weather database.
